CHANGELOG.md:886:- Added depth-2 Theramini MIDI listener (frac-0036): `my-claw/tools/theramini_midi.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `midi_to_freq`, `midi_to_name`, `parse_midi_messages`, `apply_midi_event`, `process_buffer`, `render_state`, `write_state`, `read_midi_buffer`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus frozen `MidiEvent` and mutable `MidiState` dataclasses that hold the current note, last-note timestamp, silence-start timestamp, CC map, and pitch-bend value. The listener parses raw Note On / Note Off / CC / pitch-bend bytes (including the velocity-zero Note On = Note Off and 2-byte program/channel-pressure cases), folds events into a per-cycle `MidiState`, and atomically writes `/tmp/theramini_state.json` with the existing consumer contract (`timestamp`, `is_playing`, `pitch_hz`, `pitch_note`, `pitch_confidence`, `state`, `consecutive_silence_ms`, `midi_cc`, `pitch_bend`) after passing through `senseweave.theramini_duet.normalize_theramini_state` so the duet conversation contract is preserved. `is_playing` decays to `False` after `2.0` seconds without a fresh note. Loop control gains `--device`, `--interval`, `--state-path`, `--once`, and `--max-iterations`; missing or unopenable MIDI devices fall back to the existing `state="no_device"` payload shape. `tests/test_theramini_midi.py` pins import safety, MIDI parse/apply, active-note and silent-window rendering, end-to-end fd writes, and the no-device fallback; `tests/test_theramini_listener_runtime.py`, `tests/test_theramini_duet.py`, and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:888:- Added depth-2 Tamagotchi diagnostics (frac-0035): `my-claw/tools/tamagotchi.py` now exposes frozen `PetVitalSnapshot` and `PetFleetReport` dataclasses plus typed helpers `pet_health_band`, `pet_activity_band`, `xp_to_next_stage`, `stage_progress_fraction`, `pet_attention_reasons`, `build_pet_vital_snapshot`, `build_pet_fleet_report`, and `summarize_pet_fleet_report`. Existing JSON persistence, task XP, idle decay, and GlyphWeave display contracts are preserved, while `PetManager.fleet_report()` now gives status/diagnostic callers an end-to-end health/activity/fleet summary with canonical pet ordering, aggregate XP/tasks, mean vitals, active/sleeping/attention agents, and XP leader. `tests/test_tamagotchi_depth.py` pins helper bands, frozen snapshot/report shape, JSON-safe summaries, persistence round-trip, and fractal depth >= 2; existing tamagotchi/GlyphWeave tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:890:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:892:- Added depth-2 sensory journal daemon processing (frac-0033): `my-claw/tools/sensory_journal_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers for reading fused organism state, normalizing Theramini/room/mood snapshots, detecting ordered Theramini-start, room-transient, and energy-shift events, writing through the existing `senseweave.sensory_journal` JSONL contract, and running the loop with `max_iterations` / `--once` for tests and smoke runs. `tests/test_sensory_journal_daemon.py` pins import safety, meaningful event descriptions, one-cycle journal writes, and duplicate suppression across repeated active cycles; the existing sensory journal suite and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:894:- Added depth-2 voice alias report helpers (frac-0032): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceAliasEntry` and `VoiceAliasReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_namespace`, `voice_alias_family`, `is_aliased_voice`, `iter_alias_pairs`, `aliases_for_target`, `alias_chain`, `build_voice_alias_entry`, `build_voice_alias_report`, and `summarize_voice_alias_report` so runtime/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing eleven-entry `RUNTIME_VOICE_ALIAS` table into a JSON-safe summary with ordered source/target voices, namespace counts (core vs senseweave), family counts (struck_tonal, metallic, granular, drum, other), senseweave-variant and core-alias counts, unique-target count, target-to-sources mapping, and per-alias entries flagging `is_senseweave_variant` and `is_changed`. Existing `resolve_runtime_voice_name` lookup behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins helper outputs, frozen entry/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with `resolve_runtime_voice_name`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:896:- Added depth-2 synthesis architecture registry report helpers (frac-0031): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis_architecture_registry.py` now exposes frozen `ArchitectureProfile` and `ArchitectureRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `affinity_band`, `control_span_band`, `fallback_chain`, `build_architecture_profile`, `build_architecture_registry_report`, and `summarize_architecture_registry_report` so planner/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing six-family synthesis strategy registry into a JSON-safe summary with ordered architecture IDs, phase winners, phase-ranked candidates, role-to-architecture mappings, fallback chains, macro-control defaults/span bands, high-affinity phase bands, missing coverage diagnostics, and per-architecture profiles. Existing registry entries and lookup behavior remain unchanged; `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry_depth.py` pins helper cutpoints, fallback-cycle handling, profile/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with existing lookup helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:900:- Added depth-2 accompaniment decision report helpers (frac-0029): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/accompaniment.py` now exposes frozen `AccompanimentPatternSnapshot` and `AccompanimentPlanReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `accompaniment_density_band`, `accompaniment_pattern_name`, `accompaniment_energy_band`, `frequency_register_band`, `accompaniment_transition_mode`, `summarize_pattern_events`, `build_pattern_snapshot`, `build_accompaniment_plan_report`, and `summarize_accompaniment_plan_report` so composer/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing inverse-density accompaniment path into a JSON-safe decision summary. Existing `DensityTracker`, selection, six pattern helpers, pedal, breathing, transition, and tuple contracts are preserved; `tests/test_accompaniment_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, pattern snapshot aggregation, end-to-end density/breathing/pedal report output, JSON-safe summaries, agreement with the existing helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_accompaniment.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:904:- Added depth-2 EMSD performance adjustment report helpers (frac-0027): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/emsd_performance.py` now exposes frozen `PerformanceEventSpec`, `PerformanceEventSnapshot`, and `PerformanceAdjustmentReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `amp_pressure_band`, `release_shape_band`, `brightness_shape_band`, `space_amount_band`, `build_performance_event_snapshot`, `build_performance_adjustment_report`, and `summarize_performance_adjustment_report` so diagnostics callers can resolve the existing live `render_adjustments_for_event(...)` path into operator-readable per-event and batch summaries. Existing `PerformanceAdjustments` fields and note-level playback behavior are preserved; `tests/test_emsd_performance_depth.py` pins band cutpoints, snapshot/live-adjustment parity, ordered aggregate role/voice/DSP/sample metadata, empty-sequence rejection, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end Theramini ducking and DSP propagation, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_emsd_performance.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:908:- Added depth-2 motif-lifecycle report helpers (frac-0025): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/motif_lifecycle.py` now exposes frozen `MotifLifecycleStep` and `MotifLifecycleReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lifecycle_state_index`, `build_lifecycle_step`, `canonical_lifecycle_path`, `build_lifecycle_report`, and `summarize_lifecycle_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can advance a motif through the one canonical lifecycle path and emit a JSON-safe operator summary with ordered history, current/terminal state, valid next states, canonical state counts, contour/rhythm/material deltas, and per-step state-band/material diagnostics. Existing transition rules, deterministic transformations, `advance(...)`, `MotifLifecycleManager`, and repertoire-shape recall behavior are preserved; `tests/test_motif_lifecycle_depth.py` pins the new report surface, manager end-to-end agreement, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_motif_lifecycle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:912:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:918:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:920:- Added depth-2 punctuation report helpers (frac-0019): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/punctuation.py` now exposes frozen `LanePunctuationStat` and `PunctuationReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_punctuation_stat`, `analyze_punctuation`, and `summarize_punctuation_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R6 punctuation rule once and inspect per-lane phrase-terminal outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, terminal-note count, extended-terminal count, inserted-breath count, mean terminal multiplier, mean breath milliseconds, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `PunctuationRule.apply`, and `apply_punctuation` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_punctuation_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_punctuation_depth.py` pins melody shaping, non-melodic and lane-grid-locked non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:924:- Added depth-2 metric accent report helpers (frac-0017): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/metric_accent.py` now exposes frozen `LaneMetricAccentStat` and `MetricAccentReport` dataclasses plus `lane_metric_accent_stat`, `analyze_metric_accent`, and `summarize_metric_accent_report` so diagnostics can apply the R1 rule once and inspect per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, meter, step count, shaped-step count, mean multiplier, strongest row, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `METRIC_ACCENT_4_4`, `metric_accent_table`, `MetricAccentRule.apply`, and `apply_metric_accent` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_metric_accent_depth.py` pins the new report surface and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_metric_accent_rule.py`, `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py`, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:928:- Added depth-2 render ablation helpers (frac-0015): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py` now exposes frozen `AblationCase`, `AblationResult`, and `AblationSuite` dataclasses plus `rule_identifiers`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, and `summarize_ablation_suite` so CCH-010 tooling can plan single-rule or custom ablation cases, render a full-stack baseline, execute each case through the existing `ablate()` seam, and return JSON-safe operator summaries with changed/unchanged counts. Existing `ablate()` behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_render_ablation.py` now pins suite planning, custom pair handling, summary output, and fractal depth >= 2, while debugger/listener-review and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:932:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:936:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:938:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:940:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:952:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
